petes over the same number of days.\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 840, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"No other Olympic sport competes\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 810}, {\"ngram\": \"the same number\", \"from\": 816, \"to\": 831}, {\"ngram\": \"days\", \"from\": 835, \"to\": 839}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is a mixed squad, a small squad compared to those from the last three Olympic boxing tournaments; the cycle has only been three years and since winning six medals in Tokyo in 2021, 10 of the team of 11 have turned professional.\", \"from\": 842, \"to\": 1072, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1011, \"end\": 1016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.8265387282479232, \"rank\": 0.20986466265371062, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a mixed squad\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 861}, {\"ngram\": \"a small squad\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 876}, {\"ngram\": \"the last three Olympic boxing tournaments\", \"from\": 900, \"to\": 941}, {\"ngram\": \"the cycle\", \"from\": 943, \"to\": 952}, {\"ngram\": \"three years\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 978}, {\"ngram\": \"six medals\", \"from\": 997, \"to\": 1007}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 1032, \"to\": 1040}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are other reasons that British boxers will only be competing in six of the 13 weights in Paris, but too often the valid obstructions and distractions can sound like excuses; there are no excuses, it is hard to qualify for theOlympics.\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1313, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1102, \"end\": 1109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9390730796880114e-14, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\"}, {\"begin\": 1168, \"end\": 1173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999778538, \"rank\": 2.2124162167965582e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other reasons\", \"from\": 1083, \"to\": 1096}, {\"ngram\": \"the 13 weights\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1164}, {\"ngram\": \"the valid obstructions\", \"from\": 1189, \"to\": 1211}, {\"ngram\": \"distractions\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1228}, {\"ngram\": \"excuses\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1251}, {\"ngram\": \"no excuses\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1273}, {\"ngram\": \"theOlympics\", \"from\": 1301, \"to\": 1312}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1996 and 2000 just two went, in 2004 it was just one; the packed squads from the last three Games have given a false impression that simply pulling on the vest was enough to get a golden ticket to the greatest platform in sport.\", \"from\": 1315, \"to\": 1546, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the packed squads\", \"from\": 1372, \"to\": 1389}, {\"ngram\": \"the last three Games\", \"from\": 1395, \"to\": 1415}, {\"ngram\": \"a false impression\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1445}, {\"ngram\": \"the vest\", \"from\": 1469, \"to\": 1477}, {\"ngram\": \"a golden ticket\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1511}, {\"ngram\": \"the greatest platform\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1536}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 1540, \"to\": 1545}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Tokyo, three short summers ago, the GB boxers shared the top spot for medals with the Russians, beating the mighty Cubans by one.\", \"from\": 1547, \"to\": 1679, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1550, \"end\": 1555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.8265387282479232, \"rank\": 0.20986466265371062, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"ht